<div id="content_title">ICS Petitions</div>

<blockquote>
<div id="content_text">

<table border="1" cellpadding="3" cellspacing="2" style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #66ccff;" summary="ICS Petitions">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td align="center" style="background-color: #ffffcc;"><strong>Petition</strong></td>
<td align="center" style="background-color: #ffffcc;"><strong>Purpose/ Examples<br/></strong></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="mailto:ucounsel@uci.edu?subject=Request/%20Petition%20for%20exception&amp;body=Submit%20the%20information%20below%20if%20you%20are%20requesting%20/%20petitioning%20for%20an%20exception.%0D%0A%0D%0AExamples%20of%20past%20petitions:%20Request%20for%20course%20substitution%20or%20waiver;%20Request%20to%20waive%20the%20residency%20requirement;%20Request%20for%20transfer%20credit%20for%20a%20course%20taken%20outside%20of%20UCI%20for%20which%20there%20is%20no%20articulation%20agreement;%20Request%20for%20exception%20to%20an%20administrative%20decision,%20policy,%20or%20deadline.%0D%0A%0D%0APlease%20attach%20any%20supporting%20documentation,%20if%20applicable.%0D%0A%0D%0AUCI%20Student%20ID#:%20%0D%0A%0D%0AFull%20Name:%20%0D%0A%0D%0AMajor:%20%0D%0A%0D%0ARequest:%20%0D%0A%0D%0AExplanation%20and%20Justification:%20">Undergraduate Student Petition</a></td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>To request course substitution or waiver</li>
<li>To request credit for major or general education courses taken at a college for which there is no articulation agreement</li>
<li>To waive residence requirement</li>
<li>To request exception to an administrative decision, policy or deadline</li>
</ul>
<em>Note: Supporting documentation may be required</em></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<p><a href="mailto:ucounsel@uci.edu?subject=Request%20to%20update%20Degreeworks&amp;body=Submit%20the%20information%20below%20AND%20fill%20out%20the%20attached%20DegreeWorks%20Update%20form%20if%20you%20are%20requesting%20a%20degree%20audit%20update.%0D%0A%0D%0AUCI%20Student%20ID#:%20%0D%0A%0D%0AFull%20Name:%20%0D%0A%0D%0AMajor:%20">Request DegreeWorks Update</a></p>
<p><strong>Attach this <a href="sao/DegreeWorks Update Form.pdf">DegreeWorks Update form</a> to your email</strong></p>
</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>To add or delete minor(s)</li>
<li>To clear Category VI Language other than English requirement</li>
<li>To clear Category VIII International/Global Issues</li>
<li>To apply study abroad courses to your degree audit</li>
<li>To apply transfer courses to your degree audit</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<p><a href="mailto:ucounsel@uci.edu?subject=Request%20to%20declare%20major%20specialization/%20track&amp;body=Submit%20the%20information%20below%20if%20you%20are%20requesting%20to%20declare%20or%20update%20your%20major%20specialization/%20track.%20%20ICS%20majors%20that%20require%20a%20specialization%20or%20track%20are:%20Computer%20Science,%20Computer%20Game%20Science,%20and%20Informatics.%20%20To%20find%20more%20information%20about%20specializations/tracks,%20consult%20the%20UCI%20Catalogue.%0D%0A%0D%0ANote:%20Computer%20Science%20students:%20If%20you%20entered%20UCI%20in%20Fall%202015%20or%20after,%20you%20may%20declare%201%20specialization%20only.%20%20If%20you%20entered%20UCI%20in%20Fall%202014%20or%20prior,%20you%20may%20declare%20up%20to%202%20specializations.%0D%0A%0D%0AComputer%20Game%20Science%20and%20Informatics%20students%20may%20declare%20only%20one%20track.%0D%0A%0D%0AUCI%20Student%20ID#:%20%0D%0A%0D%0AFull%20Name:%20%0D%0A%0D%0AMajor:%20%0D%0A%0D%0ASpecialization%20or%20track%20you%20would%20like%20to%20declare/change%20to:%20">Declare Major Specialization or Track</a></p>
</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>To apply specialization or track to your degree audit</li>
<li>If you need help choosing, refer to the <a href="http://catalogue.uci.edu/donaldbrenschoolofinformationandcomputersciences/#undergraduatetext">UCI Catalogue</a></li>
</ul>
<p><em>Note: <strong>Computer Science</strong> students: If you entered UCI in Fall 2015 or after, you may declare 1 specialization only.&#160;&#160;If you entered UCI in Fall 2014 or prior, you may declare up to 2 specializations.</em></p>
<p><em><strong>Computer Game Science</strong> and <strong>Informatics</strong> students may declare only one track.</em></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="https://ugradforms.ics.uci.edu/" target="_blank" title="Online ICS Prerequisite Clearing Request Form">Online Prerequisite Clearing Request</a></td>
<td>
<p>If course prerequisite(s) were satisfied via any of the following ways:</p>
<ul>
<li>AP exam credit</li>
<li>Transfer school credit for a course prerequisite</li>
<li>Access UCI credit for a course prerequisite</li>
<li>Course credit by student petition for a course prerequisite</li>
<li>Credit by Exam</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr/>
<tr>
<td>
<p><a href="mailto:ucounsel@uci.edu?subject=Request%20to%20enroll%20in%20more%20than%2020%20units&amp;body=Submit%20the%20information%20below%20if%20you%20are%20requesting%20to%20enroll%20in%20more%20than%2020%20units.%20%20To%20be%20approved,%20your%20cumulative%20GPA%20and%20your%20most%20recent%20quarter%20GPA%20must%20be%203.0%20or%20higher.%20%20No%20exceptions.%0D%0A%0D%0AUCI%20Student%20ID#:%0D%0A%0D%0AFull%20Name:%0D%0A%0D%0AMajor:%0D%0A%0D%0AQuarter%20for%20which%20you%20are%20requesting%20to%20enroll%20in%20more%20than%2020%20units%20(example%20Fall%202017):%0D%0A%0D%0AHow%20many%20units%20you%20are%20requesting%20to%20enroll%20in:%0D%0A%0D%0AWhat%20is%20the%20reason%20for%20requesting%20to%20enroll%20in%20more%20than%2020%20units?%20What%20is%20the%20additional%20course%20you%20would%20like%20to%20add?%0D%0A%0D%0A">Request Excess Units</a></p>
</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>To request enrollment of more than 20 units</li>
<li>Most recent quarterly and cumulative GPA must be 3.0 or higher</li>
<li>Excess units are <em>not</em> intended to increase waitlist options. Only submit requests if you plan on taking more than four classes</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<p><a href="mailto:ucounsel@uci.edu?subject=Request%20for%20syllabus%20review&amp;body=Submit%20the%20information%20below%20AND%20fill%20out%20the%20attached%20Syllabus%20Review%20form%20if%20you%20are%20requesting%20a%20syllabus%20review.%20%20Note:%20In%20order%20to%20qualify%20for%20a%20syllabus%20review,%20the%20course%20syllabus%20MUST%20include%20WEEKLY%20topics%20taught.%0D%0A%0D%0AUCI%20Student%20ID#:%20%0D%0A%0D%0AFull%20Name:%20%0D%0A%0D%0AMajor:%20">Request Syllabus Review</a></p>
<p><strong>Attach this <a href="sao/Syllabi_form.pdf">Syllabus Review form</a> to your email</strong></p>
</td>
<td>
<ul>
<li>Request credit for a course taken at a different institution.</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>
<p>Part-Time Study</p>
<p>Form available at Registrar's office or ICS Student Affairs</p>
</td>
<td>
<p>Must meet one of these conditions:&#160;</p>
<ul>
<li>Work 20 or more hours a week</li>
<li>Have negative health condition</li>
<li>Have significant family responsibilities</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #6699cc;"><strong>&#187;</strong></span> The "Dean's Signature"</strong></p>
<p>The Dean's Signature may be obtained at the Bren ICS Student Affairs Office.</p>
<p>Counselors are authorized to provide Dean's review and signature in all instances involving LATE add/drop/change of grading option requests done via the on-line Enrollment Exceptions system, and on other student-related forms issued by the Registrar's Office or other administrative offices.</p>


</div>
